# Storybook Conventions

## File Placement

- Colocate stories next to their component: `Button.stories.tsx` alongside `Button.tsx`.
- Name story files with the `.stories.tsx` extension.

## Story Structure

- Use CSF3 (Component Story Format 3) with a `meta` default export and named story exports:

```tsx
import type { Meta, StoryObj } from "@storybook/react";
import { Button } from "./Button";

const meta = {
  title: "Components/Button",
  component: Button,
  tags: ["autodocs"],
} satisfies Meta<typeof Button>;

export default meta;
type Story = StoryObj<typeof meta>;

export const Default: Story = {
  args: {
    children: "Click me",
  },
};

export const Disabled: Story = {
  args: {
    children: "Disabled",
    disabled: true,
  },
};
```

## Best Practices

- Add `tags: ["autodocs"]` to generate automatic documentation from props.
- Use `args` for props — this enables the Storybook controls panel.
- Group stories by folder using the `title` field: `"Components/Button"`, `"Layout/Header"`.
- Create multiple named exports for meaningful variants (e.g. `Default`, `Loading`, `WithIcon`), not just one.
- Use `satisfies Meta<typeof Component>` for type-safe meta (not `as Meta`).
